#오픈알림신청은_댓글을_남겨주세요

저번에 인기짱이였던 김치공구입니다!
ㄹㅇ후기는 쏘딜 사이트 들어가시면 보실 수 있어요🖐🏻

숙성김치는 여전히 맛있구요~
모든재료 100%국내산을 이용해서 정성껏 만든 김치입니다.

이번엔 당일제조해서 만든 생김치도 추가되었는데요~
진짜 너무너무 맛있어요!

나머지 김치들도 좋은재료로 만들어 모두 맛있습니다!

6개월 이상 숙성되면 묵은지라고도 부르구
요리하기에 딱 좋은 익힘정도입니다!
(받으셔서 기호에 맞게 더 익혀 드셔도 되구요)

🔻김치공구 상품🔻

숙성김치 2kg
당일제조 생김치 2kg
열무김치 2kg
열무 물김치 2kg
오이소박이 1kg
파김치 500g

✔️오픈일정 8월 7일 낮 12시
🚚8월 10일 화요일부터 순차출고

⏰알림신청은 댓글을 남겨주세요!

MARUBANG NOODLE & PORK
[Platter of Pork]

Since its opening in back in April, we’ve been dying to try Marubang’s new location on William St, taking residence in SunBBQ’s old spot. Marubang, previously a small restaurant located further down William St, now spans two stories with their downstairs level featuring their ala carte menu, while upstairs feature their BBQ offerings 🔥. The expansion is much welcomed looking at how busy the place is with plenty of people waiting to get a spot.

🍴🍴🍴
🐷Banjok Bossam $60 - ohyang jokbal and bosom combo, radish kimchi
🥞Haemul Kimchi Jeon $15 - kimchi, squid, mussel, clam, prawn
🍝Marubang Neng Guksu $14 - ice slushed cold broth noodle, grated radish, egg, wasabi

Of course, we were obliged to try their noodle and pork dishes. We had heard that Marubang’s bossam was to die for, and opted to try their combination plate which also includes the slow braised pork hoc for additional variety. The pork was so well spiced and perfectly fatty, melting in your mouth. Despite the fact that there was so much pork on the platter (easily enough to feed 4-5 people), we still felt like it wasn’t heavy or cloying at all! The included radish kimchi and pickled cabbage was to die for, and perfect additions to put in your fresh cabbage wrap 😋

We also ordered the kimchi pancake which was chock full of seafood (although would’ve loved just a bit more spice! 🌶) and the extra refreshing iced broth noodles, which are great to cleanse the palate between each bite of bossam.

Thanks to our dear friend @adamispotato for taking us! We can’t wait to return to try out their KBBQ section 😍

🥔 감자 수제비 맛있게 만들어 먹는 법
.
.
.
🌱 더 자세한 요리순서 TMI

큰볼에 밀가루 300ml , 물 100ml , 올리브유 1큰술 , 소금 0.5스푼을 넣고 반죽을 잘 치댄 후 냉장고에 1시간 정도 숙성시킨다 (반죽할 때 물을 한번에 넣으면 반죽이 질어질 수 있으니 반죽 상태를 보면서 물을 나눠 넣어주세요)

멸치다시마육수 800ml에 적당한 크기로 자른 감자 1개를 넣고 끓여준다

다진마늘 1스푼 , 국간장 2스푼을 넣고 끓여준다

반죽한 수제비를 얇게 떠 육수에 넣어주고 반달모양으로 자른 애호박 1/3개 , 채썬 당근 1/4개 , 송송 썰은 청양고추 1개를 넣고 끓여준다 (반죽이 냄비 바닥에 붙을수 있으니 잘 저어주세요)

간을 보고 싱거울 경우 소금 0.5스푼을 넣어준 뒤 대파 1/2대를 넣고 끓여서 마무리한다
.
.
.
.
.
